Ok, i did my little investigation, here is my project. Is this right code? Where i will see output of this code? I thought it will be processor, but it is not there. In result_worker neither. Maybe i did something wrong? When i had mistake in on_result, i saw errors in processor. And another question, after errors in on_result i could not restart project, even when i changed itag. Looks like having code in result_worker class is more easy to debug.

#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Created on 2016-04-17 23:46:02
# Project: ya_ru

from pyspider.libs.base_handler import *
import platform
import logging
import json
logger = logging.getLogger("result")

class Handler(BaseHandler):
    crawl_config = {
        'itag': 'v20'
    }

    @every(minutes=1)
    def on_start(self):
        print(platform.python_version())
        self.crawl('http://ya.ru', callback=self.index_page, fetch_type='js')

    @config(age=3)
    def index_page(self, response):
        for each in response.doc('a[href^="http"]').items():
            self.crawl(each.attr.href, callback=self.detail_page)

    @config(priority=2)
    def detail_page(self, response):
        return {
            "url": response.url,
            "title": response.doc('title').text(),
        }
    
    def on_result(self, result, task, response):
        logger.info('hello i am working')
        logger.info(result)

