> How can i change the state (es: page to first one) if i cannot reach the tablestate?

As any angular directive with a controller you can require that controller from a child directive and call its API. Have a look at the source codes of the built in directives for more details (stSort, stSearch, stPagination). The table state and the table will be updated accordingly. 

> there is a way to call directly the pipe() from my crud functions controller?

There is a way but that is not recommended as it is not the normal flow (a la Flux). user interact -> tableState change -> pipe -> table is updated.

you'll need to create a directive to access tabel api and communicate with your controller

```Javascript
app.directive('refresh',['crudService',function(crud){
   return {
     requires:'stTable',
     scope:{
        // use binding here to communicate with the external world
     }
     link:function(scope,elem,attr,table){
        
         var ts = table.tableState()  // get access to the table state
         // table.search()
         // table.sortBy()
         // table.slice()
        // ... any function offered by the api
        //table.pipe(ts)
     
     }
   }

}]);
```

I think the best in this case is you format you data collection before you bind it to the table so the rendered text match the actual field value.

in you controller
```Javascript
//assuming the actual collection is var rows ->
$scope.rowCollection = rows.map(function(val){
   return {
    //...
     birthDate:$filter('date')(val.birthDate, format, timezone)
   //...
   }
});
```

There is one dirty hack

```html
<table class="table" st-pipe="pipeFunction" ...>
....
```

In your controller:
```javascript
$scope.pipeFunction = function(tableState, ctrl)
{
    if ( !$scope.stCtrl && ctrl )
    {
        $scope.stCtrl = ctrl;
    }
                
    if( !tableState && $scope.stCtrl ) {
        $scope.stCtrl.pipe();
        return;
    }

    tableState.start = tablestate.pagination.start || 0;
    tableState.number = tablestate.pagination.number || 10;

    // get data
}
```

Then you can call `pipeFunction` in your controller to update entries from server.

