If I'm reading the developer tools in chrome correctly, when disabled is set to True that simply adds a `disabled` tag to the button. That in turn changes what css is applied. In `buttons.less` (from bootstrap) this is picked up a selector that fades the button:

```css
.btn.disabled, .btn[disabled], fieldset[disabled] .btn {
    cursor: not-allowed;
    opacity: 0.65;
    filter: alpha(opacity=65);
    -webkit-box-shadow: none;
    box-shadow: none;
}
```

